The paper deals with visual recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is a discriminative approach to compare two sets of instance vectors, which involves machine learning techniques such as classification and feature extraction, making it relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method in action and image recognition tasks, which are sub-fields of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
